### Bug Description

Starting with Strapi v5.16.1 , there seems to be a new issue affecting custom GraphQL queries.
Specifically, when querying a collection type that includes a relation field, the related data is returned as null instead of the expected fields.

### Steps to Reproduce

1. Create a simple collection type with name(text) and a relation field (manyToOne) 
2. Create the second simple collection type with a name(text) and the inverse relation
3. Create a custom query extension that is returning all requests
4. Query the auto generated requests query and the custom query extension with the same fields
5. The custom query is returning null for the relation field

### Expected Behavior

Im expecting the custom query response to have all specified fields the same way as for the autogenerated queries or until v5.16.0

### Logs

```shell

```

### Code Snippets

```json
{
    "kind": "collectionType",
    "collectionName": "requests",
    "info": {
        "singularName": "request",
        "pluralName": "requests",
        "displayName": "Requests",
        "description": ""
    },
    "options": {
        "draftAndPublish": true
    },
    "pluginOptions": {},
    "attributes": {
        "name": {
            "type": "string"
        },
        "author": {
            "type": "relation",
            "relation": "manyToOne",
            "target": "api::end-user.end-user",
            "inversedBy": "requests"
        }
    }
}
```


```json
{
  "kind": "collectionType",
  "collectionName": "end_users",
  "info": {
    "singularName": "end-user",
    "pluralName": "end-users",
    "displayName": "End users",
    "description": ""
  },
  "options": {
    "draftAndPublish": true
  },
  "pluginOptions": {},
  "attributes": {
    "name": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "requests": {
      "type": "relation",
      "relation": "oneToMany",
      "target": "api::request.request",
      "mappedBy": "author"
    }
  }
}
```

```ts
export const extension = {
    typeDefs: /* GraphQL */ `
        type Query {
            customRequest: [Request]
        }
    `,
    resolvers: {
        Query: {
            customRequest: async () => {
                const requests = await strapi.documents('api::request.request').findMany({});
                return requests;
            },
        },
    },
};

export default extension;
```

